- It is used only in `thrown.printStackTrace(new PrintWriter(writer))` — i.e., passed as an argument to `printStackTrace(PrintWriter)`.
- `printStackTrace(PrintWriter)` **does not close** the `PrintWriter`. It writes to it and returns.
- No explicit `.close()` call appears on the `PrintWriter` instance.
